The next phase.
Life is moving fast. It keeps reminding me that I am not a kid anymore, not a teenager anymore. I am a adult and I can clearly see responsibilities ahead of me. I am in a safe space right now, shadowed by my parents hard work and care but it isn't going to be the same in a couple of months. I feel immense disappointment for not really learning any  skill. Some money making skill, some important survival skill.

I don't know how to cook and clean, no Idea about finances, no idea about politics. I am not even aware of how cruel the world works. I am getting idea of it, and It's harsh. I wish to grow up soon. I wish to learn it all. But I am afraid by that time, I would be burdened with responsibilities. Most furious thing about me is how dumb I am. How I end up being the fool just because I was honest. Playing fair doesn't work here. People are strategic, I should be too. 

I want to feel complete. Independent. Forgiven. 
